did.abstract: Papers and VHS tapes of a labor activist, social justice activist, feminist, and union member

bioghist.p: Labor activist, social justice activist, feminist, and union member. Kelsey was a member or officer of various labor and social justice organizations, including the Office and Professional Employees International Union Local 8, the King County Labor Council; El Centro de la Raza; Mothers for Police Accountability, the King County Union Retirees Council, the Puget Sound Alliance for Retired Americans, and the Coalition of Labor Union Women, among others. Kelsey was also involved in the work of the Seattle City Council's World Trade Organization Accountability Review Committee as a member of its Citizens Panel on Planning and Preparedness.

scopecontent.p: Correspondence, materials related to Kelsey's activism with labor and social justice organizations, records of her membership in Local 8, boad records, interview notes, draft documents, reports, VHS tapes, and print material related to OPEIU Local 8 meetings.

scopecontent.p: Correspondence and subject files include materials related to Kelsey's activism with labor and social justice organizations, Central America issues, and women's and senior's issues. A substantial group of records documents Kelsey's work with El Centro de la Raza, a social service organization in Seattle. Materials from Kelsey's activities in the labor movement include records from her membership in Local 8 of the Office and Professional Employees International Union (Secretary-Treasurer, 1985-1989; President, 1989-2001), and to her work on the Executive Board of the King County Labor Council. Records of her work on a Citizens' Panel of the Seattle City Council's World Trade Organization Accountability Review Committee include interview notes, correspondence, draft documents, and reports on the preparation and planning for the WTO's ministerial meeting in Seattle in 1999. The collection also contains publications of organizations in which Kelsey was active, particularly the Puget Sound Alliance for Retired Americans and OPEIU Local 8.

userestrict.p: Creator's copyrights transferred to the University of Washington Libraries Special Collections.

Norma L. Kelsey video recordings and papers

scopecontent.p: VHS Videotapes of news coverage of Norma Kelsey, World Trade Organization protest (1999) news coverage and Accountability Commission tapes; Common Sense Economics Trainings; Office and Professional Employees International Union training tapes; and a video from Washington State Jobs With Justice. Print materials include a 2017 Pacific Northwest Labor History Association calendar; a speech on Kelsey's rank and file reform of OPEIU Local 8, and OPEIU Local 8 meeting materials and local information.

accessrestrict.p: VHS cassettes are open for previewing onsite in the Special Collections Reading Room only.
